</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E03AAEB8E1C42B04C8FB8B409E4185FA" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" type="comments">
<paragraph id="648080B9293A5BDE186312E36F8D1115" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99F1884A55907C424E1AD20DC72BEED8" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">
Two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="5B053CECB5516E816F0B7C06384E7B38" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leymus mollis" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis id="B4A4F14C26D91C77F8EB224922AA6D80" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">Leymus mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are recognized in North America: 
<taxonomicName id="FD40A96D483E89BA00515279600A2877" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. mollis" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mollis" subSpecies="mollis">subsp. mollis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2320E2CD4165252B7D04DE076BE5E4C1" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. villosissimus" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mollis" subSpecies="villosissimus">subsp. villosissimus</taxonomicName>
(Scribn.) 
<normalizedToken id="E6E286FA0324248D3DB9EE4DEB7B2AAA" originalValue="Á">A</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="68B0FC182E644B1CA1B4167EED7E4B1B" originalValue="Löve">Loeve</normalizedToken>
&amp; D. 
<normalizedToken id="BB8B23662694F1AC8C71476F404525A8" originalValue="Löve">Loeve</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="42D519E0D731A3AAAFC2E856B40CFDAA" author="Bowden, WM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="951 - 993" publicationUrl="10.1139/b57-080" refId="B14" refString="Bowden, WM, 1957. Cytotaxonomy of section Psammelymus of the genus Elymus. Canadian Journal of Botany 35: 951 - 993, DOI: 10.1139/b57-080" title="Cytotaxonomy of section Psammelymus of the genus Elymus." url="10.1139/b57-080" volume="35" year="1957">Bowden 1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5C1134951A66CA9D278D3902A7ACD2FF" author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="353 - 369" refId="B9" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. Leymus Hochst. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 353 - 369" title="Leymus Hochst." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4844498C93D8CE8B41C3C8A2A6E4B0CA" author="Elven, R" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" publicationUrl="http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" refId="B37" refString="Elven, R, Murray, DF, Razzhivin, VY, Yurtsev, BA, 2011. Annotated checklist of the Panarctic Flora (PAF): Vascular plants, version 1.0., http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" title="Annotated checklist of the Panarctic Flora (PAF): Vascular plants, version 1.0" url="http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" year="2011">Elven et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="64C031B1EBE9769DD024E4BC2C0E88AD" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leymus mollis subsp. villosissimus" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mollis" subSpecies="villosissimus">Leymus mollis subsp. villosissimus</taxonomicName>
is an Arctic taxon, distributed from Siberia to Greenland, and common in the low CAA, while 
<taxonomicName id="C1C5EDAC01EB9FE496FE688BE1567D78" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. mollis" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mollis" subSpecies="mollis">subsp. mollis</taxonomicName>
grows along the east and west coasts of North America, along the Arctic coast of Quebec, in some interior locations (Great Slave Lake, for example) and in Greenland (
<bibRefCitation id="6C62C160C5D316BC78CA71B920CDB6FA" author="Bowden, WM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="951 - 993" publicationUrl="10.1139/b57-080" refId="B14" refString="Bowden, WM, 1957. Cytotaxonomy of section Psammelymus of the genus Elymus. Canadian Journal of Botany 35: 951 - 993, DOI: 10.1139/b57-080" title="Cytotaxonomy of section Psammelymus of the genus Elymus." url="10.1139/b57-080" volume="35" year="1957">Bowden 1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5DE60D42DD0902CB42276472A5A7D8AE" author="Aiken, SG" journalOrPublisher="NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="35" pageNumber="58" publicationUrl="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" refId="B1" refString="Aiken, SG, Dallwitz, MJ, Consaul, LL, McJannet, CL, Boles, RL, Argus, GW, Gillett, JM, Scott, PJ, Elven, R, LeBlanc, MC, Gillespie, LJ, Brysting, AK, Solstad, H, Harris, JG, 2007. Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]. NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa, http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" title="Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]" url="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" year="2007">Aiken et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="41C83B1E50897A564BD7DAD353F607C7" author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="353 - 369" refId="B9" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. Leymus Hochst. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 353 - 369" title="Leymus Hochst." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 24 Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="5B73BBA7CA6360EE5C4249BE8C81A4D3" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. mollis" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mollis" subSpecies="mollis">
<emphasis id="2478E1F5B510FDF244BADD1E73FE9CE3" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not previously been reported from the CAA (
<bibRefCitation id="B3F6338CBCF47B439E3C5A1B08B67E82" author="Bowden, WM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="951 - 993" publicationUrl="10.1139/b57-080" refId="B14" refString="Bowden, WM, 1957. Cytotaxonomy of section Psammelymus of the genus Elymus. Canadian Journal of Botany 35: 951 - 993, DOI: 10.1139/b57-080" title="Cytotaxonomy of section Psammelymus of the genus Elymus." url="10.1139/b57-080" volume="35" year="1957">Bowden 1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B459D52DA42CBD9292F42B3853C3602D" author="Aiken, SG" journalOrPublisher="NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="35" pageNumber="58" publicationUrl="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" refId="B1" refString="Aiken, SG, Dallwitz, MJ, Consaul, LL, McJannet, CL, Boles, RL, Argus, GW, Gillett, JM, Scott, PJ, Elven, R, LeBlanc, MC, Gillespie, LJ, Brysting, AK, Solstad, H, Harris, JG, 2007. Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]. NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa, http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" title="Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]" url="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" year="2007">Aiken et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and our collection from southern Baffin Island is thus the first record for the region. The collection was made on the outer sandy floodplains of Soper Lake, where the species was uncommon; subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="B1476269E05ACD34C5FA5CD0EB204B8A" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. villosissimus" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="mollis" subSpecies="villosissimus">
<emphasis id="1E43CE44CB4F6897D2BF2FEBE4C547A2" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="38">villosissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was more common in the region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
